Nyando MP Fred Outa has been arrested for allegedly inciting Ahero Girls' Secondary School students to protest.Outa was arrested on Tuesday for demanding that their interdicted principal be brought back, leading to demonstrations.Assistant IG Joseph Keitany said the MP was addressing the students when he was ejected by Ahero police station officers."He was told to go to the station to record a statement but instead he went to the market and mobilised the youth to cause chaos," he said.He said the MP will appear at a Kisumu court on Tuesday afternoon.More to follow